The pilot reported that after takeoff from runway 31, the airplane climbed to approximately 75 
feet above ground level and encountered a downdraft. The airplane impacted the runway 
causing substantial damage. An examination of the airplane's systems revealed no anomalies. 
Prior to departure, the pilot estimated the wind as 280 degrees at 15 knots. After the accident, a 
hand held wind meter recorded the winds at 8 knots, gusting to 18 knots.
the pilot's failure to maintain aircraft control during the departure climb. Contributing factors 
included the gusty winds and the downdraft.
